Selena Gomez was admitted into a psychiatric facility in October after an emotional breakdown associated with her health according to TMZ, she has been discharged. She has been there for a month and has undergone treatment. Her health issues coincided with her ex-boyfriend, Justin Bieber’s alleged marriage to Hailey Baldwin. She has allegedly been released and according to TMZ is keeping away from public eye. Before being treated, sources say she was struggling with a low white blood cell count due to the kidney transplant she received in 2017 and had to be taken to Cedars-Sinai Medical Center in Los Angeles for treatment in September. LOS ANGELES, CA – NOVEMBER 19: Selena Gomez attends the 2017 American Music Awards at Microsoft Theater on November 19, 2017 in Los Angeles, California. Neilson Barnard/Getty Images/AFP Gomez was reportedly released from the hospital days later but was then readmitted the following week as her cell count remained low; the second admission to the hospital reportedly caused a “downward spiral” into what has been described as an emotional breakdown. She reportedly entered the mental-health facility in early October. Gomez previously checked into a psychiatric facility in 2016 to treat anxiety, depression, and panic attacks, which she said she suffered from as a side effect of lupus.